    "created_at": "2020-11-18T18:51:15Z",
    "updated_at": "2020-11-18T18:51:15Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I don't think the premise of this issue is correct.  *Most* of the metadata only depends on the compilation, but parts -- specifically, the `output` parts -- depend on the particular contract.  As such, I don't think it makes sense to treat metadata as a compilation-level thing, unless perhaps one wants to perform processing to split it into compilation-level and contract-level parts, which I don't think we want to do (we typically want to treat it as opaque).  (@gnidan?)",
